article.headline: Indiana St. 59, Ball St. 48
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. (AP) -- Marco Stinson scored 18 points to lead Indiana State to a 59-48 win over winless Ball State on Saturday. Jay Tunnell finished with 16 for the Sycamores (4-4). Ball State (0-8) was led by freshman Melvin Goins, who scored a career-high 17 points. The teams went back-and-forth in the first half, but Indiana State ended up with a 24-20 lead at halftime. The Sycamores came back in the second half and took the lead for good. Indiana State had 38 rebounds, compared to 26 for Ball State.
